-- Poland's PGE granted 1 billion zloty loan from state bank BGK
-- By Wiktor Szary
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 04:22AM EST
-- None



WARSAW, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Polish state bank BGK has granted a 1 billion zloty ($292 million) loan to utility company PGE, the bank said on Thursday.

"The aim of the loan is to ensure financing for long-term and profitable infrastructure projects," it said in a statement. The loan is due in December 2027.